``` --no-startup-id

The --no-startup-id argument of the exec command in i3wm disables
startup-notification support for a particular command. With
startup-notification, i3wm can display a small notification when an application
is launched, but this can cause delays in the startup process if many
applications are launching at once.

The --no-startup-id argument disables the startup-notification support for the
specific exec command being run, which can help speed up the startup process.
When this argument is used, i3wm will not display any startup notifications for
the application launched with the exec command.

Overall, the --no-startup-id argument can be useful in optimizing the startup
process in i3wm by disabling unnecessary notifications when launching
applications with the exec command.

